doc.field:
This collection (stacked series) of datasets is provided to the UVA Library’s Scholars’ Lab by the Office of Mapping and Geographic Information (OMAGI), and is provided AS-IS with no guarantees as regards to its accuracy or temporal currency. It pertains primarily to the infrastructure and land use within the County of Loudoun as well as related natural features. * // * The temporal extent of the datasets in the datastack is generally in the 2000-2005 range, but some datasets may include attribute data collected during previous field surveys. * // * Datasets/Layers included in this datastack (with non-exclusive list of included attributes): *
*Addresses, incl: street names, geocoding information *Agricultural Districts, incl: acreage and deed information, name of agricultural district *Bedrock *Buildings, incl: building type (see zip file for data dictionary code), creation/modification date *Census blocks 2000 incl: FIPS coding, population and # housing units per region *Street centerlines, incl: geocoding information, road construction status, agency/entity source of features *County boundaries *Drainage (surface drainage features – natural and manmade), incl: flow characterization and drainage type (see data dictionary in zip drive for coding) *Driveways arcs *Election district (as of 2000), incl: district name and number, precinct *Elementary school attendance zones (as of 2001), incl: codes for school names (see data dictionary in zip file) *Fault arcs (subsurface geologic formation, geology and surface deposits), incl: codes for type of fault and certainty in fault determination (see data dictionary in zip) *Forest and shrub cover (based on 2004 aerial photography), incl: forest type (see data dictionary in zip) *Geodetic control points (survey reference points registered with National Geodetic survey), incl: elevation in ft and m, source that created feature class (e.g. county, contract, etc.) *Census groups 2000, incl: FIPS codes, block group numbers *Historic and cultural conservation districts, incl: district name, source of feature data *High school attendance zones *Limestone conglomerate overlay *Major drainage (drainage features that drain watersheds > 650 acres), incl: drainage area *Major power lines (high tension overhead power lines, generally owned by Virginia Power) *Major roads *Major watersheds *Miscellaneous Cultural Arcs (e.g. sidewalks, dams, culverts, walls, etc.), incl: arc type (see zip for data dictionary) *Miscellaneous cultural polygons (e.g. swimming pools, athletic fields, cemetaries, etc.) *Miscellaneous cultural points (e.g. manholes, poles, towers, utility features, etc.) *Middle school attendance zones *Mountainside area classifications, incl: sensitive areas *County open space easements *County parcel boundaries, incl: area in deed (sq ft), subdivisions, unoccupied areas *Planar polygons (coincide with Loundoun County’s GIS library tile system) *Planned land use areas, incl: land use type *Post offices *psf1grid *Fire company’s first due area, incl: company name *Police company’s first due area *Rescue company’s first due area, incl: company number / name *Police stations *Properties within County-administered Quarry Notification Overlay District (land use impact of a quarry on neighboring land uses) *Road casings (e.g., parking lots, driveways, etc.), incl: classification of permeability and road type *Right of way layer supplements for areas through private property *Soils types, incl: slope, layer type *Spot elevations (ft), incl: elevation, source, date of feature creation/modification *Steep slope areas (layer identifying areas with a slope > 15%), incl: slope severity index *Structures *Sub areas *Surficial *Elevation contours, 5’ intervals *Town boundaries, incl: name of jurisdiction *Census tracts 2000 *Trees (point) *Village conservation areas (as of 2002), incl: village names *Water bodies, incl: surface elevation, water type *Water wells and pollution sources, incl:ID code, date of discovery of pollution source, pollution code categories (see data dictionary in zip) *Wet model e *Postal zip code boundaries *Official zoning ordinance, incl: zoning district, ordinance, categories (see data dictionary in zip for full descriptions)
// * These data were made available to the University of Virginia for educational and research uses only. Access is restricted to students, faculty and staff of the University of Virginia.
